doc.ContractDescription: THIS PROPOSAL BUILDS ON AND CONTINUES THE RESEARCH DESCRIBED IN LOW VOLUME FRACTION ENTROPICALLY DRIVEN COLLOIDAL ASSEMBLY (PHASE 2) (I.E., L0CA (PHASE 2)). THE DEEP ROOTS OF THE WORK (I.E., THE PHASE 1 VERSION L0CA) DERIVE FROM AN EXPERIMENTAL PROGRAM THAT WAS PEER-REVIEWED AND ACCEPTED FOR FLIGHT ON ISS; THE INSTRUMENTATION AT THE HEART OFTHE ORIGINAL FLIGHT PROPOSAL FOR ISS WAS PART OFTHE SO-CALLED THE LIGHT MICROSCOPY MODULE (LMM). MORE RECENTLY, A SCIENCE CONCEPT REVIEW (SCR) FOR L0CA (PHASE 2) WAS HELD IN JUNE 2011, AND THE PROPOSED RESEARCH WAS STRONGLY ENDORSED BY THE EXTEMAL REVIEW PANEL IN THEIR REPORT ON JUNE 14 2011; THUS, THE SCIENCE GOALS AND EXPERIMENTAL PLANS FOR THE PRESENT PROPOSAL, L0CA (PHASE 3), HAVE ALREADY BEEN CRITICALLY REVIEWED. THE CURRENT RESEARCH WILL BE INTEGRATED INTO THE HARDWARE DEVELOPED FOR THE SPACE-FLIGHTS THAT ARE N^NED BY VARIANTS OF THE TERM "ACE" (E.G., ACE-HL, ETC.). IN ADDITION, RELATED COMPLEX FLUID MEASUREMENTS HAVE BEEN CARRIED OUT IN THE BCAT-SERIES FLIGHT EXPERIMENTS. SINCE THE ORIGINAL L0CA PROPOSAL WAS SUBMITTED AND APPROVED, THE NASA BUDGET HAS BEEN IN FLUX AND SOFT MATTER SCIENCE HAS EVOLVED TOO. IN RESPONSE TO THESE DEVELOPMENTS, THE PRESENT INVESTIGATIONS ARE LEANER, WITH SMALLER BUDGETS, AND THE SCIENCE AIMS HAVE EVOLVED TO TAKE ADVANTAGE OF IMPORTANT RECENT BREAKTHROUGHS IN THE FIELD. HEREIN WE DESCRIBE THESE COMPLEX FLUID EXPERIMENTS. NOTE ALSO, WHENEVER POSSIBLE, WE WILL BE JOINING FORCES WITH OUR COLLEAGUES FROM EUROPE TO PERFORM COLLABORATIVE EXPERIMENTS WITHIN THE ESA AND NASA FACILITIES. THE PROJECT DESCRIPTION INCLUDES A SYNOPSIS OF MATERIAL THAT HAS ALREADY BEEN PEERREVIEWED AND APPROVED AS PART OFTHE EARLIER PROPOSALS NOTED ABOVE. THIS BACKGROUND MATERIAL HAS BEEN SHORTENED FROM THAT IN PREVIOUS PROPOSALS, BUT OVERLAP REMAINS. THE DESCRIPTION ALSO INCLUDES NEWER (RELATED) MATERIAL WHICH WILL LEAD TO IMPORTANT SCIENCE AND WHICH USES ACE SPACE FACILITIES, AND THE BACKGROUND SECTION ALSO DESCRIBES PROGRESS/PUBLICATIONS MADE DURING THE 2008-13 FUNDING PERIOD. THE OVERALL RATIONALE FOR THESE INVESTIGATIONS IS THAT THE ELIMINATION OF PARTICLE SEDIMENTATION EFFECTS IN MICROGRAVITY CREATES A PURELY "THERMODYNAMIC" ENVIRONMENT FOR COLLOIDAL SUSPENSIONS WHEREIN PARTICLE SIZE, SHAPE AND VOLUME FRACTION, AND INTERPARTICLE INTERACTIONS ARE THE DOMINANT DETERMINANTS OF THE ASSEMBLED STRUCTURES. THIS FEATURE ENABLES US TO MAKE NEW MATERIALS THAT DO NOT FORM ON EARTH AND TO ELUCIDATE THE EFFECTS OF GRAVITY IN SOFT MATTER SCIENCE THAT ARE MASKED IN GROUND-BASED EXPERIMENTS.
